OL,3,CNo evidence former police chief misled
OL,4,CGuernsey's Royal Court
OL,6,F"It is the Committee for Home Affairs'
OL,7,Fview that the Bailiwick must have a
OL,8,Frobust and trusted police complaints
OL,9,Fsystem, and all complaints against
OL,10,Fpolice officers must be taken
OL,11,Fseriously.
OL,13,F"As previously stated, it is also the
OL,14,FCommittee's view that Police
OL,15,FComplaints Legislation in Guernsey
OL,16,Frequires a fundamental and
OL,17,Fcomprehensive review, as a priority,
OL,18,Fto ensure it fully meets Policing
OL,19,FStandards and public requirements of
OL,20,F2025."
